Lukas is a surname which has numerous spellings; Luka, Lukas, Lukacs, Lukkas, Lukaz and many more.

==Meaning and different spellings==

Latin - Lukas - Light

Hungarian - Lukas/Lukacs - Light, the lonely Mountain

Italian - Lukas/Lucas - "the man from Lucanus"

Polish - Lukaski

Anglo-saxian - Lukas

English/American - Lucas

Lithuanian - Lukas

==Origin==
Sources indicate that the name originated from the biblical personality and gospel author Saint Luke. First common usage of the name appears Jewish in origin.<!--Wikipedia Template {{fact}} -->

